#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:5
msgid "Deep Verification"
msgstr "深度驗證"

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:7
msgid ""
"Formal verification is becoming substantially more practical for smart "
"contracts. Better tooling and accessible machine-checked semantics now make "
"it feasible to prove properties on production code that were previously out "
"of reach."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:9
msgid ""
"However, formal verification only proves that a program satisfies a "
"specified property *within its formal model*. In practice, most verification "
"work today establishes that property at only one layer of the stack. "
"Everything else (from the accuracy and completeness of the model itself, "
"through the compiler, to the EVM execution semantics), is taken on trust."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:11
msgid ""
"This distance between what is formally proved and what actually executes on "
"chain is the **verification gap**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:13
msgid ""
"**Deep verification** is the discipline of reducing that gap by formally "
"bridging as many layers as possible. The fewer unverified assumptions remain "
"in the chain, the stronger the resulting guarantee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:16
msgid "Verification Depth and Breadth"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:18
msgid "Two concepts help clarify the verification gap:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:20
msgid ""
"**Verification depth** — how far the proof carries through the stack, from a "
"high-level security property through source semantics and compiler "
"correctness down to the EVM execution model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:21
msgid ""
"**Verification breadth** — how much of the contract’s actual behavior is "
"covered: which functions, which properties, which sequences of operations, "
"and which environment assumptions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:23
msgid ""
"Every verification effort has some gap. Deep verification is the discipline "
"of reducing it to its irreducible minimum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:26
msgid "The Layers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:-1
msgid ""
"The verification stack, from high-level properties down through source\n"
"semantics, compiler correctness, and EVM semantics to deployed bytecode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:34
msgid ""
"A source-level proof establishes a property under the language’s formal "
"semantics. A bytecode-level proof establishes the analogous statement "
"against a formal EVM model. A verified compiler connects the two. The fewer "
"layers a guarantee skips by assumption, the smaller the verification gap."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:37
msgid "The Technical Foundation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:39
msgid ""
"Two of those layers already exist as public, machine-checked artifacts "
"developed in the Verifereum project using HOL4:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:41
msgid "A formal semantics for the Vyper source language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:42
msgid "A formal semantics for the EVM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:44
msgid ""
"Together they provide the mathematical foundation against which source-level "
"and bytecode-level proofs about Vyper programs can be stated. The work is "
"fully open and available in the `vyper-hol <https://github.com/verifereum/"
"vyper-hol>`_ repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:47
msgid "Current Status"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:49
msgid ""
"Source-level verification on Vyper contracts and libraries is available "
"today. Compiler verification (the critical link that connects source "
"semantics to deployed bytecode) is in active development, with substantial "
"proof engineering already underway."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deep-verification.rst:51
msgid ""
"No complete deep verification pipeline exists yet for any widely deployed "
"smart-contract language. Vyper is one of the places where the pieces are "
"actively being assembled, and the stack is already in place for meaningful "
"source-level work."
msgstr ""

